Welcome back to The Best & The Brightest. Happy Black Friday! I hope you ha=
d a wonderful Thanksgiving free of political blowups. So in the spirit of f=
ostering a well-informed electorate=E2=80=94in this case, of the few hundre=
d Democrat National Committee members who will ultimately pick the chair=E2=
=80=94I=E2=80=99ve been vetting the D.N.C. chair candidates on my pod. Earl=
ier this week, I spoke to former congressman Max Rose, who hasn=E2=80=99t a=
nnounced his candidacy but is transparently flirting with a run. Then I spo=
ke to former Maryland governor Martin O=E2=80=99Malley, who officially kick=
ed off the race last week by announcing his own bid. Rose had no problem bl=
aming the Harris campaign for the Dems=E2=80=99 losses this cycle; O=E2=80=
=99Malley, meanwhile, wouldn=E2=80=99t do so, even though a number of Democ=
ratic senate candidates outperformed the top of the ticket.

